00:00:55.001 --> 00:01:02.000
Great! Now that we have Copilot installed, let's look at some basic features.

00:01:02.001 --> 00:01:10.000
One of the most powerful features is inline code suggestions.
As you type, Copilot suggests completions.

00:01:10.001 --> 00:01:18.000
You can accept suggestions with Tab, or see alternative suggestions
with Alt+] or Alt+[.

00:01:18.001 --> 00:01:25.000
Let's write a simple function together and see Copilot in action.

00:01:25.001 --> 00:01:35.000
[Live coding demonstration: Creating a user authentication function]

00:01:35.001 --> 00:01:42.000
Notice how Copilot understood the context and suggested relevant code.

00:01:42.001 --> 00:01:50.000
This brings us to our next major topic: understanding how context works
in GitHub Copilot.

00:01:50.001 --> 00:01:58.000
Copilot looks at your open files, recent edits, and comments to provide
contextually relevant suggestions.

00:01:58.001 --> 00:02:05.000
The more descriptive your comments and variable names, the better
suggestions you'll get.

00:02:05.001 --> 00:02:13.000
Let's talk about best practices for getting the most out of Copilot.

00:02:13.001 --> 00:02:20.000
First, write clear and descriptive comments. Copilot uses these to understand
your intent.

00:02:20.001 --> 00:02:28.000
Second, use meaningful variable and function names. This helps Copilot
understand your code structure.

00:02:28.001 --> 00:02:36.000
Third, break complex problems into smaller functions. Copilot works better
with focused, single-purpose functions.

00:02:36.001 --> 00:02:45.000
Now let's discuss some advanced features, including Copilot Chat.

00:02:45.001 --> 00:02:53.000
Copilot Chat allows you to have conversations about your code directly
in your IDE.

00:02:53.001 --> 00:03:01.000
You can ask it to explain code, suggest improvements, or even write tests.

00:03:01.001 --> 00:03:10.000
Let me demonstrate how to use Copilot Chat for code review and refactoring.

00:03:10.001 --> 00:03:18.000
[Demonstration: Using Copilot Chat to refactor legacy code]

00:03:18.001 --> 00:03:25.000
As you can see, Copilot Chat can significantly speed up code understanding
and maintenance.

00:03:25.001 --> 00:03:33.000
Let's take a 5-minute break here, and when we return, we'll cover
testing with Copilot.

00:03:38.001 --> 00:03:45.000
Welcome back! Let's dive into automated testing with GitHub Copilot.

00:03:45.001 --> 00:03:53.000
Writing tests is crucial, but it can be time-consuming. Copilot can help
generate test cases.

00:03:53.001 --> 00:04:01.000
Let's write tests for the authentication function we created earlier.

00:04:01.001 --> 00:04:10.000
